Remarks.
Grube ( 1840 )
established the genus
Thysanozoon
, within the family Pseudocerotidae . Occasionally, species determinations within the genus
Thysanozoon
can be made using coloration and color pattern (
Bolaños et al. 2007
). The presence of the two external characters such as a papillated dorsal surface (unlike
Pseudobiceros
) and two male gonopores (unlike
Acanthozoon
with one male pore) placed these worms in this genus.
Thysanozoon brocchii
is a cosmopolitan species distributed from the temperate to cold seas in both the Pacific and Atlantic Oceans (
Bahia et al. 2012
;
Brusa et al. 2009
;
Bulnes et al. 2011
;
Lang 1884
;
Marcus & Marcus 1968
;
Prudhoe 1989
;
Yeri & Kaburaki 1918
).
